Tuttle first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]].<ref name=2010CensusCA/>

The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Tuttle had a population of 102. The population density was {{convert|58.0|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Tuttle was 32 (31.4%) [[White Americans|White]], 4 (3.9%) [[African Americans|African American]], 3 (2.9%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 7 (6.9%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 20 (19.6%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 36 (35.3%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 54 persons (52.9%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Tuttle CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0680882 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 4, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 30 households, out of which 8 (26.7%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 18 (60.0%) were married-couple households, 3 (10.0%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 6 (20.0%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 3 (10.0%) had a male householder with no partner present. 3 households (10.0%) were one person, and 1 (3.3%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 3.4.<ref name=DP1/> There were 25 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (83.3% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Tuttle CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0680882 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 4, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 24 people (23.5%) under the age of 18, 14 people (13.7%) aged 18 to 24, 19 people (18.6%) aged 25 to 44, 31 people (30.4%) aged 45 to 64, and 14 people (13.7%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 42.0{{nbsp}}years. There were 57 males and 45 females.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 36 housing units at an average density of {{convert|20.5|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 30 (83.3%) were occupied. Of these, 10 (33.3%) were owner-occupied, and 20 (66.7%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

